As for the task system, this is how I THINK it should be:</p>

<p>You get a task to take care of some complot somwhere far away. The plots can be anything from summoning a demon to stealing some artifact from some temple to just plain bandits somewhere.</p>

<p>You will be forced to travel there trough old means, meaning boats and walking. </p>

<p>ALL the way there you will be constantly ambushed by both, enemies related to your target as well as zone defined ambushers. Example of zone defined ambushes can be orcs on the commonlands or a pack of lions on the Karanas. Maybe one huge giant... This would all be things that will sneak on you and you will have to fight, no sneaking around will work as they will spawn already with your group on top of the agro list.</p>

<p>So, once you get to the point you where sent to there you will find the enemy you where sent to take care off, but he will only spawn once you get there, he wont spawn before so someone can take care of him first.</p>

<p>Currently the world is huge, so i KNOW that you can do the system inteligent enough to make sure your destination wont be where other adventurers are hunting. Of course the system should take into account what expancions are owned by each member just to make sure it wont send them into a land they cant visit.</p>

